1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,833
There were all ages,
boys fifteen to twenty

2
00:00:05,875 --> 00:00:10,416
And elderly men, like the one
arrested for assaulting a woman

3
00:00:10,416 --> 00:00:13,041
Some had fired guns

4
00:00:13,083 --> 00:00:14,791
Another was there
over cigarettes

5
00:00:15,125 --> 00:00:16,583
And another for a
mobile phone charge

6
00:00:17,416 --> 00:00:19,625
There were many charges inside

7
00:00:23,291 --> 00:00:27,416
Interviewer: How were the relations
in the three cells you stayed in...

8
00:00:27,458 --> 00:00:29,291
In each one for a
few days at a time?

9
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:32,125
How did you see the
relationships among the prisoners?

10
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:34,958
Were their relationships good?

11
00:00:34,958 --> 00:00:38,333
Was there help among them,
did they talk to one another?

12
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:42,333
There was some
talking but not much

13
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,375
They could ask
about certain things

14
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:48,500
About the charges and
reasons for detention

15
00:00:49,541 --> 00:00:51,791
Or whether you had
been before the judge

16
00:00:51,916 --> 00:00:54,041
What they had done to you
and what they would do

17
00:00:54,041 --> 00:00:55,750
And whether the judge
had spoken to you or not

18
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:58,750
That kind of question

19
00:01:00,708 --> 00:01:04,458
Interviewer: Did ISIS plant any spies
among you in these three rooms?

20
00:01:04,458 --> 00:01:05,500
No

21
00:01:08,125 --> 00:01:11,750
Interviewer: Did any of your
companions die here or get tortured?

22
00:01:11,958 --> 00:01:16,708
Do you recall a name—someone
you heard was tortured and later died...

23
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:19,666
Or was tortured, died, and
never returned to the cell?

24
00:01:20,583 --> 00:01:22,125
No, no, none

25
00:01:22,166 --> 00:01:26,833
They took someone out on a
theft charge, stealing a motorcycle

26
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:33,541
They took him down, flogged him,
then brought him back to the hall

27
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:38,208
Two days later they removed
him—they did nothing else to him

28
00:01:39,166 --> 00:01:43,333
Interviewer: How did you receive him
when he came back from the torture room...

29
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:44,500
Flogged?

30
00:01:44,791 --> 00:01:46,416
Did you take care of him?

31
00:01:46,416 --> 00:01:49,541
Yes, I and two
others looked after him

32
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:52,791
We cared for him

33
00:01:52,791 --> 00:01:56,958
His back was almost
black from the torture

34
00:01:58,708 --> 00:02:01,333
We comforted him,
saying, You’ll get out later

35
00:02:01,375 --> 00:02:05,041
And this beating is better
than having your hand cut off

36
00:02:05,541 --> 00:02:09,583
We encouraged him—he rested and
slept, and next day they took him out

37
00:02:14,666 --> 00:02:17,083
Regarding ISIS videos,
did they show you any?

38
00:02:17,541 --> 00:02:20,666
Did they gather you
and make you watch?

39
00:02:20,708 --> 00:02:23,000
Their execution videos

40
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,291
Or hand amputations

41
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:27,791
If they showed them,
how did you feel?

42
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:30,458
No one could speak

43
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:34,458
They made us watch things
outside, not in the prison

44
00:02:35,458 --> 00:02:39,416
They gathered people and
showed how they amputated hands

45
00:02:39,416 --> 00:02:40,666
Or stoned people

46
00:02:41,166 --> 00:02:43,208
And threw them off buildings

47
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:47,166
We saw all of that because
our house was in Dawasa

48
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:50,833
When they threw
people, I could see them

49
00:02:51,375 --> 00:02:53,416
I also saw the stonings

50
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:56,625
And the hand amputations too

51
00:02:57,250 --> 00:03:01,000
They forced people
to gather and watch

52
00:03:01,041 --> 00:03:03,166
They did it in the street
so people would gather

53
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:06,750
So aircraft wouldn’t
spot and bomb them

54
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:13,791
Interviewer: At age
fifteen, a minor child

55
00:03:14,041 --> 00:03:16,666
Forced to see these
scenes every day

56
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:18,625
Right at your doorstep

57
00:03:18,666 --> 00:03:25,291
That tall Orzdi Bak building
they pushed people off

58
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:26,958
A famous building in Mosul

59
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,541
How did you feel
at that young age?

60
00:03:32,083 --> 00:03:33,708
Well, honestly

61
00:03:35,791 --> 00:03:38,916
Absolutely no one
could talk to them

62
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:42,375
They gathered crowds—why
did they do it in the street?

63
00:03:42,625 --> 00:03:44,416
So everyone would gather

64
00:03:44,625 --> 00:03:46,791
And it would be
a lesson to others

65
00:03:47,791 --> 00:03:52,666
When they amputated my
hand, it was to warn the rest

66
00:03:52,916 --> 00:03:54,416
So no one would do it

67
00:03:54,541 --> 00:03:55,958
Or would fear doing it

68
00:03:56,416 --> 00:03:59,125
They did it in the
street to scare people

69
00:03:59,541 --> 00:04:01,916
To terrify children and women

70
00:04:07,583 --> 00:04:09,250
Interviewer: While
you were in this prison

71
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:14,208
Was this prison shelled
while you were inside?

72
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,625
Did they leave you
alone at night and go out?

73
00:04:16,625 --> 00:04:19,541
Because they feared an
airstrike so they wouldn't die

74
00:04:20,208 --> 00:04:24,500
At night only a
few people stayed

75
00:04:25,916 --> 00:04:27,208
Three to four people

76
00:04:27,791 --> 00:04:29,666
And the rest all
left, they didn't stay

77
00:04:30,416 --> 00:04:34,000
A small number stayed so
the place wouldn't be empty

78
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:36,333
So no one could mess with them

79
00:04:37,083 --> 00:04:41,458
As for the rest

80
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:45,291
The senior officials didn't
stay in the same place

81
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:46,625
They were afraid
it might be bombed

82
00:04:47,041 --> 00:04:50,041
When we were here there
was no shelling on this prison

83
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:53,875
They didn't stay here—they
were afraid and went elsewhere

84
00:04:54,916 --> 00:04:57,750
They hid in houses
among families

85
00:04:58,125 --> 00:04:59,291
And in shops

86
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,416
That's how it was

87
00:05:06,166 --> 00:05:10,791
Interviewer: Did you or any of your
companions try to escape from the prison?

88
00:05:11,291 --> 00:05:12,625
I wanted to escape

89
00:05:14,208 --> 00:05:16,083
I reached the side of the door

90
00:05:16,666 --> 00:05:19,083
With a small move I could
have opened it and escaped

91
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:22,708
But fearing they would kill
me, I stayed and didn't escape

92
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:27,541
Interviewer: If you had known your
fate and the sentence you would receive

93
00:05:27,541 --> 00:05:29,250
Would you have escaped?

94
00:05:29,291 --> 00:05:31,375
Yes I would have escaped and not stayed
